HEADWORD: Octad
<hw>Oc"tad</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/, the
number eight.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An atom or
radical which has a valence of eight, or is octavalent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A group of eight things.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Octaedral</ent>⟦br⟧
